Package edu.umass.cs.msocket

This package contains the MSocket and MServerSocket classes used for client and server side mSocket communications, respectively.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MultipathInterface
    This class defines the interface for multipath operations
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AcceptConnectionQueue
    Class implements a queue for the accepted MSockets in the MServerSocket.
    BackgroudMultiPathWritingThread
    This class implements the threads to do background writes for the default multipath data scheduling policy.
    BackgroundEmptyQueueThread
    This class implements the thread to empty the queue, if no further write occurs to empty the queue
    BackgroundWritingThread
    This class implements the threads to do background writes for the default multipath data scheduling policy.
    BackgroundWritingThread2Path
    This class implements the threads to do background writes for the default multipath data scheduling policy.
    ByteRangeInfo
    This class stores byte ranges of the data and the socket object, on which the data was initially transmitted.
    ConnectionInfo
    This class keeps the state associated for MSocket like socket maps, connection state.
    ConnectionToProxyServer
    This class implements the connection to the proxy.
    ControlMessage
    Implements the setup control message format.
    DataMessage
    This class defines the data message format, every data is sent encapsulated in the data message.
    FlowIDToControllerMapping
    This class implements a UDP controller for an interface on the client side.
    FlowPath
    This class defines a FlowPath
    FlowPathResult
    Returns the result of flowpath addition or migration.
    InBufferHeapImpl
    This class implements the Inbuffer of the MSocket.
    InBufferOutOrder
    This class implements the Inbuffer of the MSocket.
    InBufferStorageChunk
    This class defines the structure of inbuffer storage chunks.
    InBufferStorageChunkComparator
    Inbuffer chunk comparator, to store the inbuffer chunks in sorted order in inbuffer as priority queue.
    InternalMSocket
    This class defines an InternalMSocket used by MServerSocket for its connections with MSocket clients.
    KeepAliveStaticThread
    Singleton keep alive thread class, and also keeps timer time.
    MServerSocket
    This class implements the MSeverSocket.
    MServerSocketController
    This class implements the internals of MServerSocket.
    MSocket
    This class implements the MSocket, applications can use MSocket to connect to a listening server
    MSocketConstants
    This class keeps the constants needed for MSocket.
    MSocketInstrumenter
    Used to instrument the times of various code segments in the msocket.
    MWrappedInputStream
    This class implements the InputStream of the MSocket.
    MWrappedOutputStream
    This class implements the Output stream of the MSocket
    OutBuffer
    This class implements the Output buffer of MSocket.
    ProxyInfo
    This class keeps the information about each proxy at the server side.
    ResendIfNeededThread
    This class implements a thread that resends the data, in orderly manner, after the migrations.
    RetransmitTask
    This class implements a timer to retransmit a message over a UDP channel.
    SetupControlMessage
    This class implements the setup control message format, serialization and de-serialization.
    SingleSocketReadReturnInfo
    Class keeps the information returned by single socket read.
    SocketInfo
    This class keeps the information about each flowpath.
    TemporaryTasksES  
    UDPControllerHashMap
    This class stores the Hashmap of UDP controllers running on different interfaces on a MSocket client side.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MSocket.MSocketType
    Denotes the type of connection msocket client wants to establish, MSOCKET_SERVER establishes connection to msocket server.
    MultipathPolicy
    This class defines a MultipathPolicy

This package contains the MSocket and MServerSocket classes used for client and server side mSocket communications, respectively.
